		<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-235">
				<div id="div-comment-235" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/73fe00032b8192875e5c394b503c0156?s=60&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D60&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-60 photo' height='60' width='60' />			<cite class="fn">Ricky Face Person</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://betterds3.ciebiera.net/why/#comment-235">
			May 3, 2013 at 3:56 am</a>		</div>

		<p>In the future could BetterDS3 end up replacing Motioninjoy completely, so that it isn&#8217;t necessary at all to even initially install the drivers?</p>
<p>Also, another helpful hint for other users might be to block off the Motionijoy exe files with Windows Firewall.</p>
<p>From start menu, search for &#8220;Firewall&#8221; and select Windows Firewall with Advanced Security</p>
<p>Choose Outbound Rules from the tree at the left.</p>
<p>Choose New Rule&#8230; from the menu at the right.</p>
<p>New Outbound Rule Wizard opens. This is really easy now:</p>
<p>a. Select Program as rule type.</p>
<p>b. Select the program&#8217;s EXE file.</p>
<p>c. Choose Block the connection.</p>

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/why/?replytocom=235#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-235", "235", "respond", "56")'>Reply</a>		</div>
